This paper is primarily focused on intrusion detection in network traffic data, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper proposes a new neural network architecture that combines the GRU model with SVM, which is a machine learning algorithm commonly used in classification tasks. Therefore, the paper is likely to be relevant to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), neural networks (cs.NE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and social and information networks (cs.SI) due to the use of recurrent neural networks and machine learning algorithms.
